lead_paragraph: An article on Oct. 15 about education as an issue in the election for California governor referred incorrectly to a link between Dan Schnur, a Republican political consultant, and a 1993 campaign for a ballot measure to create a voucher system for public schools. He took no role in the 1993 campaign; it was managed by another consultant, Ken Khachigian. This correction was scheduled for publication in October but was misplaced.
abstract: Correction: Oct 15, 1998, article about education as issue in California gubernatorial race misstated role of political consultant Dan Schnur
